  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The stout goes in the batter, not as a flavour you will notice immediately, but as a structural contribution. The liquid from the beer adds moisture, the carbon dioxide in the beer lightens the crumb slightly, and the maltiness of stout deepens the chocolate in the same direction that espresso does, without the coffee flavour. Use any dry stout; the beer does not need to be expensive."
          }
        ]
      },
